# Copy to `.env.local` (gitignored) for local dev against a real Home Assistant
# Restart `npm run dev` after editing.

# REQUIRED: Home Assistant URL (must be reachable from your dev machine)
#
# Examples:
#   Local network:     http://homeassistant.local:8123      (easiest, default)
#   Static IP:         http://192.168.1.50:8123
#   Public domain:     https://ha.yourdomainname.com
#   Docker bridge:     http://homeassistant:8123
#
# Troubleshooting WebSocket failures (esp. Windows):
# - *.local often unreliable for WebSockets on Windows — use LAN IP instead
# - Use http:// for plain HTTP, https:// for HTTPS (must match your HA setup)
# - Self-signed HTTPS? Open the URL in your browser once and accept the cert first
# - Behind reverse proxy (Cloudflare/nginx)? Use direct LAN URL here, not public hostname
#
# With VITE_HASS_URL set, `npm run dev` proxies `/api/*` to HA so camera streams and
# Skydark photos (`/api/skydark_calendar/photo/…`) don’t 404 on localhost:5173.
#
VITE_HASS_URL=http://homeassistant.local:8123

# OPTIONAL: Long-lived access token (avoids OAuth popup every dev restart)
#
# To generate: Home Assistant → Profile (⚙️ bottom left) → Security →
# Long-lived access tokens → Create token
#
# ⚠️  SECURITY: Never commit this token to Git. Keep .env.local in .gitignore.
#
# VITE_HASS_ACCESS_TOKEN=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...
